1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:01:20,001
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:02:49,415 --> 00:02:51,625
I don't know anything
about solving mysteries.

3
00:02:51,626 --> 00:02:52,626
I'm not meant for that.

4
00:02:52,627 --> 00:02:56,588
I think I hear rustling
in the ceiling and walls.

5
00:02:56,589 --> 00:02:58,966
Are you guys really sure
about the Paranormal Club?

6
00:02:58,967 --> 00:03:00,885
Don’t you want the Q.E.D. Club?

7
00:03:01,553 --> 00:03:03,346
Lori, help me!

8
00:03:07,183 --> 00:03:08,183
Oh, my God.

9
00:03:15,149 --> 00:03:17,068
I did not expect you to figure it out.

10
00:03:17,485 --> 00:03:19,904
The Q.E.D. Club

11
00:03:20,446 --> 00:03:23,782
is the one and only detective club
in Clark University.

12
00:03:23,783 --> 00:03:26,077
So, once we solve the case...

13
00:03:26,494 --> 00:03:28,913
your main task is to write about it

14
00:03:29,372 --> 00:03:30,706
and post it on your blog.

15
00:03:30,707 --> 00:03:33,375
You want me to be the club chronicler?

16
00:03:33,376 --> 00:03:34,460
Something like that.

17
00:03:58,568 --> 00:03:59,777
Get them out of here.

18
00:04:14,459 --> 00:04:15,918
Go back to your classrooms.

19
00:04:15,919 --> 00:04:17,921
- Leave.
- Go back, go back.

20
00:04:23,009 --> 00:04:24,009
Come in.

21
00:04:24,427 --> 00:04:25,427
Come in?

22
00:04:25,511 --> 00:04:26,511
Why?

23
00:04:27,180 --> 00:04:28,431
To investigate this case.

24
00:04:29,641 --> 00:04:30,266
Come on!

25
00:04:30,475 --> 00:04:31,559
Seriously?

26
00:04:33,645 --> 00:04:34,854
Do I look like I'm joking?

27
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:37,398
You’re already a member
of the Q.E.D. Club.

28
00:04:38,441 --> 00:04:41,110
Consider this
our first official case together.

29
00:04:41,361 --> 00:04:42,361
Come on!

30
00:04:42,820 --> 00:04:44,364
We’re not allowed to enter here.

31
00:04:44,864 --> 00:04:45,864
Oh!

32
00:04:47,006 --> 00:04:48,675
Haven’t I told you that I…

33
00:04:49,327 --> 00:04:50,912
and by extension, the club...

34
00:04:51,287 --> 00:04:53,498
works as a consultant
for the campus police.

35
00:04:54,499 --> 00:04:56,250
The chief is a good acquaintance of mine.

36
00:04:56,668 --> 00:05:00,380
I helped him out in a couple
of other baffling cases on campus.

37
00:05:03,174 --> 00:05:04,341
Loki!

38
00:05:04,342 --> 00:05:05,009
Chief!

39
00:05:05,343 --> 00:05:06,427
You're already here.

40
00:05:07,428 --> 00:05:10,389
I already got the gift your dad gave me,

41
00:05:10,390 --> 00:05:12,266
last week, on my birthday.

42
00:05:12,558 --> 00:05:14,811
I wanted to thank him, but…

43
00:05:14,894 --> 00:05:16,270
he’s abroad.

44
00:05:16,437 --> 00:05:18,189
Just tell him I said thank you.

45
00:05:18,564 --> 00:05:19,941
Yeah! Sure, chief!

46
00:05:20,733 --> 00:05:21,733
- Sure.
- Loki...

47
00:05:22,235 --> 00:05:26,239
I’m sorry I asked you to come,
but I really need your help.

48
00:05:29,075 --> 00:05:30,118
Ah, she's with me.

49
00:05:30,952 --> 00:05:33,246
She’s the newest member
of the Q.E.D. Club.

50
00:05:34,288 --> 00:05:35,373
And this is her...

51
00:05:35,790 --> 00:05:36,790
first case.

52
00:05:37,625 --> 00:05:40,377
- Oh, by the way, chief. She is...
- Lorelei Rios.

53
00:05:40,378 --> 00:05:41,629
Just call me Lori.

54
00:05:42,463 --> 00:05:44,966
I’m Chief Gareth Estrada.

55
00:05:45,633 --> 00:05:48,678
Head of the campus police
here in Clark University.

56
00:05:50,096 --> 00:05:51,096
Chief.

57
00:05:53,599 --> 00:05:54,599
Yeah.

58
00:05:55,351 --> 00:05:56,811
- Ma’am.
- Oh, okay.

59
00:06:01,774 --> 00:06:02,774
After you.

60
00:06:05,265 --> 00:06:07,184
♪ Shadows. ♪

61
00:06:08,099 --> 00:06:10,810
♪ Creeping slowly through the dark. ♪

62
00:06:11,576 --> 00:06:15,620
♪ Watching, blocking, like. ♪

63
00:06:15,621 --> 00:06:19,167
♪ You can't even take a step. ♪

64
00:06:20,055 --> 00:06:23,641
♪ Every cry, every shake. ♪

65
00:06:23,666 --> 00:06:26,835
♪ Only walls reflect the ache. ♪

66
00:06:26,883 --> 00:06:29,843
♪ All the echoes burn inside. ♪

67
00:06:29,844 --> 00:06:34,348
♪ Like fire and bullets in the past. ♪

68
00:06:35,521 --> 00:06:37,741
♪ Listen to the warnings. ♪

69
00:06:38,735 --> 00:06:41,421
♪ Threats are drawing near. ♪

70
00:06:42,229 --> 00:06:45,899
♪ This is not the world you thought. ♪

71
00:06:46,644 --> 00:06:49,270
♪ You would know. ♪

72
00:06:49,295 --> 00:06:51,756
♪ Listen to the warnings. ♪

73
00:06:52,718 --> 00:06:54,845
♪ Open up your eyes. ♪

74
00:06:56,341 --> 00:06:59,886
♪ This is not the world you thought. ♪

75
00:07:00,666 --> 00:07:03,210
♪ You would know. ♪

76
00:07:03,211 --> 00:07:08,049
♪ Listen to the warnings. ♪

77
00:07:15,598 --> 00:07:16,641
Don’t just stand there.

78
00:07:16,849 --> 00:07:17,975
We got some work to do!

79
00:07:20,770 --> 00:07:22,646
Do your job as the Q.E.D. chronicler

80
00:07:22,647 --> 00:07:24,565
and start writing down
whatever happens here.

81
00:07:27,485 --> 00:07:28,903
What are the details, chief?

82
00:07:30,613 --> 00:07:32,824
According to the report from my team…

83
00:07:33,574 --> 00:07:36,702
the victim’s name is Isaac Santino.

84
00:07:37,495 --> 00:07:39,372
He’s the President of the Lavoisier Club.

85
00:07:40,623 --> 00:07:41,916
The body’s still warm.

86
00:07:42,375 --> 00:07:43,584
There’s no...

87
00:07:44,293 --> 00:07:46,963
signs of rigor mortis yet.

88
00:07:47,672 --> 00:07:48,672
Our estimate

89
00:07:48,714 --> 00:07:50,675
is that he died under an hour ago.

90
00:07:51,634 --> 00:07:53,970
He died due to severe blood loss,

91
00:07:55,555 --> 00:07:57,140
stab wounds on his flank.

92
00:07:58,391 --> 00:07:59,183
Obviously.

93
00:07:59,308 --> 00:08:00,308
And...

94
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:03,354
we recovered the victim’s phone,

95
00:08:03,729 --> 00:08:04,730
far from the body.

96
00:08:05,565 --> 00:08:06,565
We suspect...

97
00:08:06,899 --> 00:08:09,359
the victim was calling for help.

98
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:11,737
The perpetrator saw it and kicked it away.

99
00:08:12,446 --> 00:08:15,031
I’ll send this to digital forensics

100
00:08:15,032 --> 00:08:18,953
to find out who the victim last called

101
00:08:18,995 --> 00:08:20,037
and texted.

102
00:08:21,330 --> 00:08:23,082
We might still find some clues.

103
00:08:28,421 --> 00:08:29,755
Have you seen this, chief?

104
00:08:40,850 --> 00:08:42,935
This isn’t just a random bloodstain.

105
00:08:44,270 --> 00:08:45,021
Could it be…

106
00:08:45,271 --> 00:08:48,107
the victim wrote down
the perpetrator’s name?

107
00:08:48,649 --> 00:08:49,649
Close.

108
00:08:51,986 --> 00:08:53,237
Those are not letters…

109
00:08:54,071 --> 00:08:55,114
but numbers.

110
00:08:58,367 --> 00:09:01,996
These numbers are probably clues
to the identity of the perpetrator.

111
00:09:04,749 --> 00:09:07,960
Why didn’t he just write
the name directly?

112
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:12,256
Well, the perpetrator
could return to the crime scene

113
00:09:12,381 --> 00:09:14,675
and see his name still written there.

114
00:09:15,092 --> 00:09:17,929
That’s why he used a code,
just in case that happened.

115
00:09:18,304 --> 00:09:21,891
Could it be the letters
correspond to the perpetrator’s name?

116
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,310
I thought about that, too.

117
00:09:24,852 --> 00:09:26,729
But the letter combinations don’t match.

118
00:09:29,774 --> 00:09:30,774
Besides...

119
00:09:31,525 --> 00:09:32,860
that would be too easy.

120
00:09:33,945 --> 00:09:35,195
It defeats the purpose

121
00:09:35,196 --> 00:09:37,156
of why you would use codes
in the first place.

122
00:09:38,241 --> 00:09:39,961
I’ve got all the content from
Isaac's phone.

123
00:09:40,201 --> 00:09:41,494
From Isaac’s phone.

124
00:09:42,036 --> 00:09:43,329
According here…

125
00:09:43,955 --> 00:09:49,126
Isaac texted three people
with the same message.

126
00:09:49,710 --> 00:09:50,835
And it says,

127
00:09:50,836 --> 00:09:52,796
"I know what you did.

128
00:09:52,797 --> 00:09:56,424
Meet me in the chem lab at lunch.

129
00:09:56,425 --> 00:09:58,886
If you don’t want others to know."

130
00:10:00,096 --> 00:10:03,723
No fingerprints were found
on Isaac’s phone

131
00:10:03,724 --> 00:10:04,850
except his own.

132
00:10:05,351 --> 00:10:07,644
Which is logical

133
00:10:07,645 --> 00:10:11,148
that he was the only one who texted them.

134
00:10:12,316 --> 00:10:13,693
One of them is the suspect.

135
00:10:15,486 --> 00:10:17,280
Who were the people he messaged, chief?

136
00:10:17,613 --> 00:10:20,365
Henry Ochoa, Genesis Cabangon,

137
00:10:20,366 --> 00:10:21,409
and John Bautista.

138
00:10:27,540 --> 00:10:28,582
I think I know who did it.

139
00:10:31,085 --> 00:10:32,085
What?

140
00:10:32,420 --> 00:10:33,504
Are you serious?

141
00:10:33,963 --> 00:10:36,590
We’ve only been at the crime scene
for a few minutes,

142
00:10:36,632 --> 00:10:39,051
but you already know who the killer is?

143
00:10:41,345 --> 00:10:42,722
Who is he, Loki?

144
00:10:45,516 --> 00:10:47,351
I want to talk to the suspects first.

145
00:10:47,935 --> 00:10:49,603
I wanna test my theory first.

146
00:10:50,187 --> 00:10:50,813
Well...

147
00:10:50,938 --> 00:10:51,938
I'll have them called.

148
00:10:53,941 --> 00:10:54,775
For questioning.

149
00:10:54,817 --> 00:10:55,817
Got it.

150
00:11:05,202 --> 00:11:07,330
So, you’re the new assistant?

151
00:11:08,247 --> 00:11:09,373
New assistant?

152
00:11:10,041 --> 00:11:12,293
Did Loki have an assistant before, chief?

153
00:11:13,002 --> 00:11:13,627
Why?

154
00:11:13,628 --> 00:11:16,380
You don’t believe
he had someone else before?

155
00:11:17,631 --> 00:11:18,631
Kind of.

156
00:11:19,216 --> 00:11:20,217
All along

157
00:11:20,426 --> 00:11:23,554
I thought he was doing it alone
as a wannabe detective.

158
00:11:24,722 --> 00:11:26,515
Well, to be honest...

159
00:11:26,974 --> 00:11:30,519
Loki used to be more approachable
than he is now.

160
00:11:31,103 --> 00:11:32,188
After he was left alone,

161
00:11:32,813 --> 00:11:33,856
he became cold.

162
00:11:34,482 --> 00:11:36,901
He doesn’t care about dealing with people,

163
00:11:37,318 --> 00:11:40,196
that’s why I was surprised
to see you here.

164
00:11:42,323 --> 00:11:43,657
If I may ask...

165
00:11:43,866 --> 00:11:45,993
what happened to his former assistant?

166
00:11:46,994 --> 00:11:48,704
I don’t know how to say this to you.

167
00:11:50,396 --> 00:11:51,814
Let’s just say that...

168
00:11:52,301 --> 00:11:53,969
she left Loki.

169
00:11:55,461 --> 00:11:57,088
I look forward to hear your story.

170
00:11:58,422 --> 00:12:00,550
Please get back to me as soon as you can.

171
00:12:01,005 --> 00:12:02,005
Regards.

172
00:12:02,346 --> 00:12:02,846
Loki.

173
00:12:03,010 --> 00:12:04,010
Is it Rhea?

174
00:12:04,178 --> 00:12:05,721
Chief, they’re here.

175
00:12:19,318 --> 00:12:21,070
Is it true someone killed Isaac?

176
00:12:22,071 --> 00:12:23,071
You are?

177
00:12:23,322 --> 00:12:24,573
Genesis Cabangon.

178
00:12:25,157 --> 00:12:27,451
I’m the treasurer of the Lavoisier Club.

179
00:12:27,910 --> 00:12:30,371
Like me, they’re officers, too.

180
00:12:30,788 --> 00:12:32,957
Henry Ochoa, vice president of the club.

181
00:12:33,207 --> 00:12:35,000
John Bautista, secretary.

182
00:12:36,001 --> 00:12:40,047
I called you here
because your president was found dead

183
00:12:40,214 --> 00:12:41,841
here in the Chemistry Lab.

184
00:12:42,550 --> 00:12:45,219
You were the last people Isaac messaged.

185
00:12:46,345 --> 00:12:48,055
I did receive it, but...

186
00:12:48,431 --> 00:12:50,015
I didn’t understand it, so…

187
00:12:50,349 --> 00:12:51,725
I just ignored it.

188
00:12:52,518 --> 00:12:53,519
Same with me.

189
00:12:53,853 --> 00:12:55,653
I thought it was just a wrong send
from Isaac.

190
00:12:55,896 --> 00:12:57,648
I know he messaged me,

191
00:12:58,107 --> 00:12:59,525
but I didn’t reply to him.

192
00:13:00,151 --> 00:13:01,694
One of you is definitely lying.

193
00:13:02,111 --> 00:13:05,284
Are you saying
the three of us killed Isaac?

194
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:07,240
That’s right.

195
00:13:07,616 --> 00:13:09,042
One of you is the perpetrator.

196
00:13:09,785 --> 00:13:11,287
And I know who he is...

197
00:13:12,204 --> 00:13:13,330
but I won’t tell you

198
00:13:13,831 --> 00:13:15,458
until we hear your statements.

199
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:16,876
Wait, wait, wait.

200
00:13:17,168 --> 00:13:19,128
You’re putting a serious accusation on us.

201
00:13:19,295 --> 00:13:20,295
What’s your basis?

202
00:13:20,629 --> 00:13:21,714
That text message?

203
00:13:21,982 --> 00:13:23,941
Just one text message?

204
00:13:23,966 --> 00:13:24,966
That’s it?

205
00:13:25,426 --> 00:13:26,719
That’s exactly why you're here.

206
00:13:27,928 --> 00:13:29,889
The conclusions will depend

207
00:13:30,639 --> 00:13:31,765
on what you say.

208
00:13:33,684 --> 00:13:37,187
I want to know
where you were from 12 to 1 p.m.,

209
00:13:37,188 --> 00:13:38,622
when the crime happened.

210
00:13:38,647 --> 00:13:40,524
I was in the bathroom during that time.

211
00:13:40,733 --> 00:13:42,985
My stomach wasn’t feeling good, so...

212
00:13:43,319 --> 00:13:44,612
I didn’t get out right away.

213
00:13:45,321 --> 00:13:46,489
Can someone confirm that?

214
00:13:47,239 --> 00:13:50,116
I went to the 4th floor bathroom
to relieve my stomach pain

215
00:13:50,117 --> 00:13:51,744
because there weren’t many people there.

216
00:13:52,036 --> 00:13:54,830
But I didn’t see anyone else
enter the bathroom.

217
00:13:55,122 --> 00:13:56,207
In other words...

218
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:58,250
you don’t have an alibi.

219
00:13:59,084 --> 00:14:00,084
How 'bout you?

220
00:14:02,129 --> 00:14:03,756
I’d just finished eating lunch then.

221
00:14:04,924 --> 00:14:07,593
I was on the rooftop smoking.

222
00:14:07,968 --> 00:14:12,014
I had just lit it
when I got the call from the police.

223
00:14:12,932 --> 00:14:14,600
Were you with someone else at that time?

224
00:14:15,893 --> 00:14:17,603
The rooftop is restricted right now.

225
00:14:18,103 --> 00:14:20,064
There was drama there the other day

226
00:14:20,648 --> 00:14:21,815
that’s why I was alone.

227
00:14:22,066 --> 00:14:23,066
Still...

228
00:14:23,150 --> 00:14:24,150
no alibi.

229
00:14:24,527 --> 00:14:25,527
And you?

230
00:14:28,989 --> 00:14:30,032
Stone benches.

231
00:14:31,408 --> 00:14:34,995
Like I said earlier,
I was reviewing because we had a quiz.

232
00:14:35,871 --> 00:14:37,831
Is anyone there with you
while you were reviewing?

233
00:14:39,333 --> 00:14:40,333
No.

234
00:14:40,501 --> 00:14:42,210
I never had anyone with me

235
00:14:42,211 --> 00:14:43,295
when I’m reviewing.

236
00:14:43,921 --> 00:14:45,214
I get distracted easily.

237
00:14:45,798 --> 00:14:47,423
But I remember,

238
00:14:47,424 --> 00:14:49,718
there were a lot of people
on the benches nearby.

239
00:14:50,511 --> 00:14:51,761
You can ask them.

240
00:14:51,762 --> 00:14:52,762
Although...

241
00:14:52,888 --> 00:14:54,890
I’m not sure
if they remember my face.

242
00:14:56,850 --> 00:14:57,850
Weak alibi.

243
00:15:00,980 --> 00:15:03,440
None of you have a perfect alibi.

244
00:15:04,191 --> 00:15:05,191
Which means...

245
00:15:05,651 --> 00:15:07,319
all of you are still suspects.

246
00:15:08,821 --> 00:15:09,821
Genesis!

247
00:15:09,905 --> 00:15:11,105
Do you know anything about it?

248
00:15:11,907 --> 00:15:12,449
No...

249
00:15:12,450 --> 00:15:13,701
I don't know anything.

250
00:15:15,578 --> 00:15:16,578
So...

251
00:15:16,996 --> 00:15:18,414
who do you think the culprit is?

252
00:15:19,248 --> 00:15:19,832
Huh?

253
00:15:20,124 --> 00:15:22,875
I’m here to document and observe.

254
00:15:22,876 --> 00:15:24,795
Why am I the one you're asking?

255
00:15:25,296 --> 00:15:26,296
Lorelei...

256
00:15:26,380 --> 00:15:28,966
You have to earn the trust
of the campus police.

257
00:15:29,174 --> 00:15:31,302
We’re going to face more of this
in the future.

258
00:15:33,178 --> 00:15:34,178
Fine.

259
00:15:35,055 --> 00:15:36,807
But I really don't know.

260
00:15:37,474 --> 00:15:39,101
Everyone says they have an alibi.

261
00:15:40,269 --> 00:15:41,269
Of course.

262
00:15:42,021 --> 00:15:45,149
No criminal
would just admit to their crime.

263
00:15:45,649 --> 00:15:47,067
Unless there’s solid evidence.

264
00:15:47,568 --> 00:15:48,777
The question is…

265
00:15:49,528 --> 00:15:52,364
how will we get the evidence?

266
00:15:53,073 --> 00:15:55,576
Why am I the one you're asking?

267
00:15:55,784 --> 00:15:56,868
If in the first place,

268
00:15:56,869 --> 00:15:59,455
you already know who the real culprit is.

269
00:15:59,955 --> 00:16:01,707
It’s not enough to know the name.

270
00:16:02,791 --> 00:16:03,791
So tell me…

271
00:16:04,793 --> 00:16:06,837
how do we get the culprit to confess?

272
00:16:07,838 --> 00:16:08,838
Think!

273
00:16:12,134 --> 00:16:14,678
Rack your brain
until something rings a bell!

274
00:16:16,722 --> 00:16:18,974
But if you change your mind,
let me know, okay?

275
00:16:19,183 --> 00:16:20,559
It's fun there. I promise.

276
00:16:26,231 --> 00:16:28,942
Why didn’t I hear the lunch break bell?

277
00:16:29,610 --> 00:16:30,611
Maybe it’s broken?

278
00:16:42,539 --> 00:16:43,582
School bell.

279
00:16:47,544 --> 00:16:48,544
That’s it!

280
00:16:49,088 --> 00:16:50,255
I know how.

281
00:16:56,095 --> 00:16:57,096
Genesis.

282
00:16:57,638 --> 00:16:58,638
Henry.

283
00:16:58,764 --> 00:16:59,764
John.

284
00:17:00,307 --> 00:17:03,644
If you were really at the place
you said earlier…

285
00:17:04,269 --> 00:17:07,439
which one of you heard the school bell?

286
00:17:09,108 --> 00:17:10,109
Of course!

287
00:17:10,651 --> 00:17:13,278
Who wouldn’t hear something that loud...

288
00:17:14,947 --> 00:17:16,782
They didn’t hear the school bell!

289
00:17:19,868 --> 00:17:20,869
That means…

290
00:17:21,412 --> 00:17:23,288
one of them is the real killer.

291
00:17:23,914 --> 00:17:24,707
Actually...

292
00:17:24,915 --> 00:17:26,583
you said the opposite.

293
00:17:27,251 --> 00:17:30,170
Whoever says they heard the school bell…

294
00:17:30,421 --> 00:17:32,131
is most likely the real culprit.

295
00:17:32,256 --> 00:17:33,256
Huh?

296
00:17:34,383 --> 00:17:35,592
What do you mean?

297
00:17:36,301 --> 00:17:38,637
The school bell was broken at lunchtime,

298
00:17:38,804 --> 00:17:40,097
that’s why it didn’t ring.

299
00:17:40,514 --> 00:17:43,349
And because the perpetrator was busy

300
00:17:43,350 --> 00:17:44,852
killing the victim,

301
00:17:45,227 --> 00:17:46,645
he didn’t notice it.

302
00:17:47,479 --> 00:17:48,479
No!

303
00:17:48,939 --> 00:17:50,315
It was just an honest mistake!

304
00:17:50,691 --> 00:17:51,691
Okay?

305
00:17:51,942 --> 00:17:53,302
Maybe I’m remembering something...

306
00:17:53,652 --> 00:17:54,820
from yesterday.

307
00:17:56,321 --> 00:17:57,321
No.

308
00:17:58,365 --> 00:17:59,658
It was really you who did it.

309
00:18:00,159 --> 00:18:01,160
You killed Isaac.

310
00:18:01,952 --> 00:18:02,952
Huh?

311
00:18:03,537 --> 00:18:04,537
How?

312
00:18:05,289 --> 00:18:06,623
Before the victim died,

313
00:18:07,082 --> 00:18:09,501
he reveal the murderer’s name
through a dying message.

314
00:18:10,294 --> 00:18:11,545
A series of numbers...

315
00:18:12,379 --> 00:18:14,840
3-2-1-0-1-4-1-6.

316
00:18:16,049 --> 00:18:19,386
How are the numbers related to Genesis?

317
00:18:29,062 --> 00:18:30,731
If we pair up these numbers...

318
00:18:31,190 --> 00:18:35,027
we get 32, 10, 14 and 16.

319
00:18:35,611 --> 00:18:39,156
Each number corresponds
to an element in the periodic table.

320
00:18:39,907 --> 00:18:41,241
32, Germanium.

321
00:18:42,201 --> 00:18:43,327
10, Neon.

322
00:18:43,660 --> 00:18:44,912
14, Silicon.

323
00:18:45,037 --> 00:18:46,413
And 16, Sulfur.

324
00:18:47,456 --> 00:18:48,916
Each element has a symbol.

325
00:18:50,876 --> 00:18:52,169
Ge, Germaninum.

326
00:18:52,544 --> 00:18:54,046
Ne, Neon.

327
00:18:54,254 --> 00:18:55,631
Si, Silicon.

328
00:18:55,798 --> 00:18:57,257
And S, Sulfur.

329
00:19:53,021 --> 00:19:54,105
It was you, Genesis.

330
00:19:54,106 --> 00:19:55,106
Huh?

331
00:19:57,401 --> 00:19:58,402
This is a frame-up!

332
00:19:59,152 --> 00:20:00,904
I’m not the one who killed Isaac!

333
00:20:01,363 --> 00:20:03,699
Maybe one of them is framing me!

334
00:20:03,907 --> 00:20:05,200
Don’t involve us in that!

335
00:20:05,492 --> 00:20:07,910
We didn’t do anything wrong.
I can’t do that.

336
00:20:07,911 --> 00:20:10,997
- Huh? You’re dragging us into this?
- I'm not the killer. Trust me.

337
00:20:10,998 --> 00:20:13,332
- What did you do to Isaac?
- Believe me, it’s a frame-up.

338
00:20:13,333 --> 00:20:14,625
If that’s not true,

339
00:20:14,626 --> 00:20:16,545
explain the stain of blood on your sleeve.

340
00:20:18,213 --> 00:20:21,091
Genesis, we need your uniform.
Please take it off!

341
00:20:21,341 --> 00:20:22,634
Mr. Cabangon.

342
00:20:23,010 --> 00:20:25,887
We’re inviting you to the police station
for questioning.

343
00:20:25,888 --> 00:20:29,224
You may call your parents or your lawyer.

344
00:20:29,933 --> 00:20:30,809
You two,

345
00:20:30,893 --> 00:20:32,686
- go back to your rooms!
- Let go of me!

346
00:20:36,273 --> 00:20:37,393
I had nothing to do with it.

347
00:20:37,782 --> 00:20:39,263
Believe me.

348
00:20:42,154 --> 00:20:46,116
What do you think
was Genesis’ motive for killing him?

349
00:20:47,743 --> 00:20:50,343
I noticed earlier that some chemicals
were missing from the shelf.

350
00:20:51,163 --> 00:20:52,789
And Isaac noticed that, too.

351
00:20:53,123 --> 00:20:53,916
But he was not sure

352
00:20:53,917 --> 00:20:55,918
which of the three suspects
is the culprit.

353
00:20:57,127 --> 00:20:59,171
So he messaged the three suspects...

354
00:20:59,421 --> 00:21:01,632
to find out who would reply.

355
00:21:02,591 --> 00:21:03,591
Unfortunately...

356
00:21:04,217 --> 00:21:06,428
he was killed
before the culprit was fully revealed.

357
00:21:07,596 --> 00:21:09,640
But why is that such a big deal?

358
00:21:10,307 --> 00:21:12,100
You killed someone…

359
00:21:12,476 --> 00:21:14,186
for such a petty reason?

360
00:21:15,354 --> 00:21:16,605
I was thinking the same thing.

361
00:21:17,356 --> 00:21:19,816
Why would Genesis steal those chemicals?

362
00:21:19,942 --> 00:21:21,735
Who’s he selling them to?

363
00:21:24,112 --> 00:21:26,740
This is probably much bigger
than we think.

364
00:21:27,491 --> 00:21:29,700
- Gosh!
- Genesis!

365
00:21:29,701 --> 00:21:30,953
- What's happening?
- Help him!

366
00:21:31,787 --> 00:21:33,956
- Genesis, are you okay?
- Don't you want to help him?

367
00:22:03,568 --> 00:22:05,404
Moriya...

368
00:22:15,497 --> 00:22:17,082
Yes, sir. Why did you call?

369
00:22:17,958 --> 00:22:22,587
Chief, as President of Clark University,

370
00:22:23,296 --> 00:22:27,342
it is my responsibilty
to protect the name of the school.

371
00:22:28,510 --> 00:22:30,011
I want to make sure

372
00:22:30,012 --> 00:22:34,766
the issues happening here
don’t get out easily.

373
00:22:35,517 --> 00:22:38,854
Make sure this doesn’t reach the media.

374
00:22:42,149 --> 00:22:43,149
Yes.

375
00:22:43,442 --> 00:22:44,484
Understood, sir.

376
00:22:52,409 --> 00:22:55,162
The investigation reached its conclusion.

377
00:22:55,912 --> 00:22:58,664
The real culprit
behind Isaac Santino’s death

378
00:22:58,665 --> 00:23:01,293
was identified as Genesis Cabangon,

379
00:23:01,877 --> 00:23:04,337
Treasurer of the Lavoisier Club.

380
00:23:06,006 --> 00:23:07,382
The revelation was shocking.

381
00:23:08,091 --> 00:23:12,137
No one expected him
to be involved in that kind of crime.

382
00:23:13,805 --> 00:23:15,140
Everyone was shocked.

383
00:23:15,599 --> 00:23:17,768
But before justice could proceed,

384
00:23:18,060 --> 00:23:20,187
something unexpected happened.

385
00:23:20,979 --> 00:23:22,313
Just as Mr. Cabangon

386
00:23:22,314 --> 00:23:24,900
was about to be turned over
to the authorities,

387
00:23:25,233 --> 00:23:28,028
he died under circumstances
that remain unclear.

388
00:23:29,696 --> 00:23:32,115
What we thought was the end of the case

389
00:23:32,407 --> 00:23:35,494
turned into another mystery
with no answers.

390
00:23:36,787 --> 00:23:39,623
The truth about Isaac’s death
may have surfaced,

391
00:23:39,790 --> 00:23:43,001
but the ending leaves us
with a lingering sense of uncertainty...

392
00:23:43,418 --> 00:23:45,294
reminding us that sometimes,

393
00:23:45,295 --> 00:23:47,254
even when answers are found,

394
00:23:47,255 --> 00:23:49,591
peace can still feel out of reach.

395
00:24:07,567 --> 00:24:08,567
Loki!

396
00:24:08,860 --> 00:24:11,613
Look, my post already has a lot
of reactions and comments.

397
00:24:17,702 --> 00:24:18,702
Loki?

398
00:24:19,162 --> 00:24:20,205
Lori!

399
00:24:21,748 --> 00:24:22,833
Yes, come in!

400
00:24:23,083 --> 00:24:24,292
Hello, Tita.

401
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:25,960
Hey.

402
00:24:26,211 --> 00:24:27,045
Hey.

403
00:24:27,046 --> 00:24:31,298
I brought you food
so you don’t have to go out.

404
00:24:31,299 --> 00:24:32,551
Thank you, Tita.

405
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:34,760
Hey, Loki...

406
00:24:36,304 --> 00:24:37,430
What happened to him?

407
00:24:37,848 --> 00:24:38,890
Why is he like that?

408
00:24:39,266 --> 00:24:41,058
I don’t know, Tita.

409
00:24:41,059 --> 00:24:42,602
He’s been like that for a while now.

410
00:24:44,146 --> 00:24:45,230
Did you reject him?

411
00:24:45,522 --> 00:24:46,958
Is that why Loki’s acting like that?

412
00:24:46,982 --> 00:24:49,484
Tita Martha, what are you talking about?

413
00:24:50,152 --> 00:24:51,862
I’m just kidding.

414
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:54,281
Because...

415
00:24:54,990 --> 00:24:57,075
I’ve seen him like that before.

416
00:24:59,703 --> 00:25:01,079
He once came home...

417
00:25:01,830 --> 00:25:04,457
looking like the world
had collapsed on him.

418
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,751
He couldn’t talk properly.

419
00:25:07,502 --> 00:25:08,712
He just stared into space.

420
00:25:09,337 --> 00:25:12,007
And he kept mentioning a woman’s name.

421
00:25:13,884 --> 00:25:15,468
I can’t remember the name anymore.

422
00:25:19,139 --> 00:25:20,473
Worse than someone heartbroken.

423
00:25:24,019 --> 00:25:26,938
Before I forget, I have good news for you.

424
00:25:28,899 --> 00:25:31,276
Your father is coming to visit next week.

425
00:25:32,152 --> 00:25:33,861
He called me earlier,

426
00:25:33,862 --> 00:25:37,865
he said he has a meeting
in Angeles City next week,

427
00:25:37,866 --> 00:25:41,077
so he might stop by to visit you.

428
00:25:45,207 --> 00:25:46,791
Why don’t you seem happy?

429
00:25:48,335 --> 00:25:49,335
Yeah.

430
00:25:49,502 --> 00:25:51,755
Thank you again for the food, Tita.

431
00:25:52,714 --> 00:25:53,714
Of course.

432
00:25:53,798 --> 00:25:54,798
Alright.

433
00:25:55,008 --> 00:25:58,428
Better eat it while it’s hot. Okay?

434
00:25:58,803 --> 00:26:01,389
Alright, I’ll leave you to eat. Okay?

435
00:26:01,435 --> 00:26:02,474
Thanks.

436
00:26:02,475 --> 00:26:03,642
Okay. Take care.

437
00:26:10,607 --> 00:26:11,524
Loki!

438
00:26:11,525 --> 00:26:14,945
Come on,
let’s eat the food Tita Martha sent.

439
00:26:17,781 --> 00:26:18,990
Hey, Loki!

440
00:26:19,658 --> 00:26:20,658
Huh?

441
00:26:22,077 --> 00:26:23,077
What time is it?

442
00:26:23,995 --> 00:26:25,080
7 p.m.

443
00:26:30,669 --> 00:26:31,920
I fell asleep again.

444
00:26:33,672 --> 00:26:36,132
I wasted my precious time
by making my self idle.

445
00:26:37,175 --> 00:26:38,175
Wait...

446
00:26:38,301 --> 00:26:40,387
you were asleep this whole time?

447
00:26:40,929 --> 00:26:41,929
Yup.

448
00:26:42,055 --> 00:26:43,807
You can sleep with your eyes open?

449
00:26:44,808 --> 00:26:45,808
Yes!

450
00:26:46,226 --> 00:26:47,560
I’ve learned that skill

451
00:26:47,936 --> 00:26:49,896
to escape my boring classes.

452
00:26:50,397 --> 00:26:52,440
I can sleep
without my teachers noticing it.

453
00:26:54,985 --> 00:26:57,737
I thought you were just zoning out again.

454
00:26:57,988 --> 00:27:00,448
Maybe you’re still thinking
about that M thing.

455
00:27:02,826 --> 00:27:04,786
Well, I was.

456
00:27:05,578 --> 00:27:07,789
Until Hypnos cradled me into his arms.

457
00:27:08,665 --> 00:27:09,958
I need to do some work.

458
00:27:10,709 --> 00:27:13,086
Loki, you need to eat.

459
00:27:13,420 --> 00:27:16,673
How can you finish everything
you need to do when you’re out of energy?

460
00:27:20,135 --> 00:27:21,135
Okay.

461
00:27:21,803 --> 00:27:22,803
- Fine.
- Okay.

462
00:27:26,474 --> 00:27:27,474
What's this?

463
00:28:13,938 --> 00:28:15,273
It's so unfair.

464
00:28:16,274 --> 00:28:18,443
Isaac just wanted to know the truth.

465
00:28:18,902 --> 00:28:20,195
But he was killed.

466
00:28:59,859 --> 00:29:02,654
They were able to extract messages
from Genesis' phone.

467
00:29:03,446 --> 00:29:04,489
And apparently...

468
00:29:05,782 --> 00:29:09,661
he's been selling stolen chemicals
to different unregistered numbers.

469
00:29:10,245 --> 00:29:12,705
Who would even buy those chemicals?

470
00:29:13,623 --> 00:29:16,042
And in our school lab, of all places?

471
00:29:16,292 --> 00:29:17,710
That we don’t know yet.

472
00:29:18,128 --> 00:29:20,130
That’s why we needed to talk to Genesis.

473
00:29:20,922 --> 00:29:22,132
But he is...

474
00:29:22,507 --> 00:29:24,174
gone, unfortunately.

475
00:29:24,175 --> 00:29:27,595
I’ve been meaning to ask,
what’s the update on him?

476
00:29:28,054 --> 00:29:29,889
That leads me to my second update.

477
00:29:30,265 --> 00:29:32,058
According to the autopsy report,

478
00:29:32,142 --> 00:29:35,437
a broken needle tip
was found lodged in his nape.

479
00:29:36,062 --> 00:29:37,980
Traces of succinylcholine,

480
00:29:37,981 --> 00:29:39,690
a fast-acting paralytic,

481
00:29:39,691 --> 00:29:42,235
were detected in this area.

482
00:29:42,819 --> 00:29:44,528
That can only be done with force

483
00:29:44,529 --> 00:29:48,199
by someone in close proximity to him
at that time.

484
00:29:48,616 --> 00:29:49,993
Unlikely by accident.

485
00:29:52,245 --> 00:29:55,665
Does that mean
he was killed to silence him?

486
00:29:57,375 --> 00:29:58,710
But who?

487
00:29:59,002 --> 00:30:02,172
There were a lot of students
when he was arrested in the hallway.

488
00:30:02,672 --> 00:30:04,299
And the police was holding him.

489
00:30:04,632 --> 00:30:06,467
Considering these developments,

490
00:30:06,468 --> 00:30:11,931
we can therefore conclude that Genesis
was merely a pawn in this grand game.

491
00:30:14,434 --> 00:30:16,603
Anyway, my class starts in five minutes.

492
00:30:17,187 --> 00:30:18,313
Let's meet later.

493
00:30:19,647 --> 00:30:20,647
Okay.

494
00:30:35,163 --> 00:30:36,915
Moriya...

495
00:30:38,791 --> 00:30:39,959
Lorelei Rios?

496
00:30:42,420 --> 00:30:43,420
Sorry...

497
00:30:43,463 --> 00:30:44,463
do I know you?

498
00:30:44,714 --> 00:30:46,257
I'm Margarette Fernandez.

499
00:30:46,424 --> 00:30:47,842
You can just call me Maggie.

500
00:30:48,009 --> 00:30:49,529
I’m a Senior Legal Management student.

501
00:30:49,761 --> 00:30:50,803
Nice to meet you.

502
00:30:51,804 --> 00:30:52,931
Nice to meet you.

503
00:30:53,640 --> 00:30:55,391
I've read the Q.E.D. blog.

504
00:30:55,558 --> 00:30:56,726
I’m a big fan.

505
00:30:57,143 --> 00:30:59,979
The chemistry lab case
was brilliantly solved and written.

506
00:31:00,897 --> 00:31:02,732
Thank you. Much appreciated.

507
00:31:02,941 --> 00:31:05,902
Is there anything I
or we can help you with?

508
00:31:06,236 --> 00:31:08,905
We can talk about it later
in the clubroom.

509
00:31:09,572 --> 00:31:11,616
I think I’m the one who can help you.

510
00:31:13,326 --> 00:31:16,871
You don't look like the type of person
who enjoys solving mysteries.

511
00:31:17,664 --> 00:31:18,748
Be honest with me.

512
00:31:19,582 --> 00:31:21,459
Were you forced to join that club?

513
00:31:22,252 --> 00:31:23,252
Sorry, but...

514
00:31:23,586 --> 00:31:25,380
why is that any of your business?

515
00:31:26,130 --> 00:31:27,715
I just want to help you.

516
00:31:28,424 --> 00:31:30,552
You won’t gain anything by joining that.

517
00:31:31,636 --> 00:31:33,555
Leave the Q.E.D. Club.

518
00:31:34,347 --> 00:31:37,350
Staying close to Loki
will only bring you tragedy.

519
00:31:37,850 --> 00:31:38,851
Sorry, but…

520
00:31:39,102 --> 00:31:40,102
who are you?

521
00:31:40,311 --> 00:31:42,313
And how did you know Loki?

522
00:31:43,022 --> 00:31:46,359
You could say I'm the closest thing
to a friend he was capable of having.

523
00:31:47,569 --> 00:31:49,903
If you think Loki and I
are in a relationship,

524
00:31:49,904 --> 00:31:51,030
you’re wrong.

525
00:31:51,406 --> 00:31:53,366
I’m just a regular Q.E.D. Club member,

526
00:31:53,658 --> 00:31:55,535
there’s nothing romantic between us.

527
00:31:55,952 --> 00:31:58,955
I’m not a threat
to whatever’s going on between you two.

528
00:31:59,330 --> 00:32:00,915
So if you’ll excuse me…

529
00:32:02,375 --> 00:32:05,503
Hasn’t he told you
what happened to the former member?

530
00:32:09,340 --> 00:32:11,551
I see he hasn't told you about her.

531
00:32:12,343 --> 00:32:13,595
And yet you’re here...

532
00:32:14,345 --> 00:32:15,805
risking your life for him?

533
00:32:17,682 --> 00:32:19,559
I'm not risking my life for anyone.

534
00:32:28,276 --> 00:32:29,319
I read your blog.

535
00:32:31,195 --> 00:32:32,238
Shorten it a bit.

536
00:32:33,740 --> 00:32:35,658
Students have short attention spans.

537
00:32:37,076 --> 00:32:39,704
Long sentences can bore readers.

538
00:32:43,499 --> 00:32:44,499
Are you listening?

539
00:32:45,460 --> 00:32:46,460
Sorry.

540
00:32:47,337 --> 00:32:48,671
Is there something bothering you?

541
00:32:50,381 --> 00:32:52,467
Someone came up to me earlier.

542
00:32:52,800 --> 00:32:55,762
Gave me a warning
about joining Q.E.D Club.

543
00:32:56,387 --> 00:32:57,639
She said...

544
00:32:58,014 --> 00:33:01,184
she's the closest thing
to a friend you were capable of having.

545
00:33:02,602 --> 00:33:03,602
She?

546
00:33:06,522 --> 00:33:08,816
For a moment I thought
you were referring to my brother.

547
00:33:09,776 --> 00:33:10,943
Brother?

548
00:33:12,070 --> 00:33:13,529
You have a sibling here?

549
00:33:14,489 --> 00:33:15,489
Yup.

550
00:33:17,116 --> 00:33:18,242
What’s his name?

551
00:33:18,660 --> 00:33:19,660
Thor?

552
00:33:19,869 --> 00:33:22,080
Like that superhero in the comics?

553
00:33:24,082 --> 00:33:25,082
Yup.

554
00:33:25,583 --> 00:33:26,583
Huh?

555
00:33:29,754 --> 00:33:31,089
Excuse me?

556
00:33:31,339 --> 00:33:33,591
Is this the Q.E.D. clubroom?

557
00:33:34,050 --> 00:33:35,592
If you’re familiar with
the English alphabet

558
00:33:35,593 --> 00:33:36,760
and you know how to read...

559
00:33:36,761 --> 00:33:38,304
Yes! This is it.

560
00:33:39,347 --> 00:33:40,932
Please, have a seat.

561
00:33:41,599 --> 00:33:42,725
How can we help you?

562
00:33:43,851 --> 00:33:44,894
Thank you.

563
00:33:53,152 --> 00:33:55,571
I’m Madonna Barcelon.

564
00:33:56,280 --> 00:33:58,782
My friends recommended you

565
00:33:58,783 --> 00:34:01,327
because they read your blog
the other day.

566
00:34:01,619 --> 00:34:03,913
They said you’re good at solving cases.

567
00:34:04,122 --> 00:34:05,707
Well, thank you.

568
00:34:06,290 --> 00:34:08,751
So what case do you want us to solve?

569
00:34:09,627 --> 00:34:10,461
So...

570
00:34:10,586 --> 00:34:12,713
do you know the Clark U Confessions page

571
00:34:12,714 --> 00:34:15,841
where students post anonymously

572
00:34:15,842 --> 00:34:19,011
about anything related
to Clark University?

573
00:34:20,722 --> 00:34:22,807
Someone posted there yesterday.

574
00:34:23,349 --> 00:34:24,392
I feel...

575
00:34:25,017 --> 00:34:26,394
like it’s aimed at me.

576
00:34:28,646 --> 00:34:29,646
Wait...

577
00:34:29,731 --> 00:34:30,815
let me show you.

578
00:34:37,697 --> 00:34:39,614
"Who's the self-proclaimed model student

579
00:34:39,615 --> 00:34:42,535
dates someone new almost every day?

580
00:34:42,994 --> 00:34:46,289
They say she’s entertaining
all her suitors at the same time.

581
00:34:46,330 --> 00:34:48,416
And here’s more gossip.

582
00:34:48,708 --> 00:34:52,335
She’s also planning to use
her sickening charm

583
00:34:52,336 --> 00:34:55,089
to run in the next
student council elections.

584
00:34:55,548 --> 00:34:56,466
Have a guess?

585
00:34:56,466 --> 00:34:57,466
Comment it now.

586
00:35:00,553 --> 00:35:02,680
It seems like the post is aimed at you.

587
00:35:03,389 --> 00:35:04,431
Excuse me?

588
00:35:04,432 --> 00:35:05,808
Not surprising.

589
00:35:06,684 --> 00:35:07,684
Loki.

590
00:35:08,352 --> 00:35:10,354
Our client just wants to know...

591
00:35:10,938 --> 00:35:14,442
who really made the post.

592
00:35:14,984 --> 00:35:16,027
Right, Madonna?

593
00:35:16,694 --> 00:35:17,694
Actually...

594
00:35:18,279 --> 00:35:21,866
I already have an idea
who might’ve leaked that info.

595
00:35:22,492 --> 00:35:25,286
I only told three friends about it.

596
00:35:26,454 --> 00:35:27,454
First question.

597
00:35:28,790 --> 00:35:30,833
Are these so-called friends of yours...

598
00:35:31,667 --> 00:35:32,877
part of your circle?

599
00:35:34,045 --> 00:35:35,045
No!

600
00:35:35,671 --> 00:35:37,381
One of them is my classmate.

601
00:35:37,673 --> 00:35:39,884
The other one is my theater mate.

602
00:35:40,134 --> 00:35:42,470
The last one is my music club mate.

603
00:35:43,012 --> 00:35:45,223
I don’t think they know each other yet.

604
00:35:45,932 --> 00:35:47,016
Second question...

605
00:35:48,059 --> 00:35:50,728
what do you think is the motive
behind the blind item?

606
00:35:54,232 --> 00:35:54,899
Ah!

607
00:35:55,191 --> 00:35:56,484
Maybe...

608
00:35:56,776 --> 00:35:58,736
they’re jealous of my beauty!

609
00:35:58,778 --> 00:36:01,322
That’s why they want to spread my secret.

610
00:36:01,781 --> 00:36:02,949
Or maybe...

611
00:36:03,282 --> 00:36:05,659
they’re ruining my reputation

612
00:36:05,660 --> 00:36:08,621
because I’m running
for student council next year!

613
00:36:10,289 --> 00:36:11,289
So, that’s it.

614
00:36:11,707 --> 00:36:13,751
What advice can you give me?

615
00:36:16,337 --> 00:36:17,421
If I were you...

616
00:36:17,922 --> 00:36:20,675
confront your friends, one by one.

617
00:36:21,008 --> 00:36:24,428
Because if they’re really your friends,

618
00:36:24,554 --> 00:36:26,263
then one of them will come forward,

619
00:36:26,264 --> 00:36:28,431
and confess
and settle whatever differences

620
00:36:28,432 --> 00:36:29,892
- you have...
- Boring!

621
00:36:31,686 --> 00:36:35,189
Why don’t you expose this friend of yours
in a more entertaining way?

622
00:36:35,606 --> 00:36:36,774
Entertaining?

623
00:36:38,901 --> 00:36:40,152
There’s no guarantee

624
00:36:40,653 --> 00:36:41,863
that this friend

625
00:36:42,154 --> 00:36:44,991
will come clean by merely talking to her.

626
00:36:46,033 --> 00:36:47,285
She’ll deny to death.

627
00:36:47,743 --> 00:36:49,662
So why don’t you set a trap for her.

628
00:36:50,329 --> 00:36:51,372
Lure her in...

629
00:36:51,914 --> 00:36:52,957
and capture her.

630
00:36:53,875 --> 00:36:55,334
So how?

631
00:36:56,294 --> 00:36:57,294
How about this?

632
00:36:59,130 --> 00:37:01,048
Tell a secret to each of your friends

633
00:37:01,757 --> 00:37:02,757
but make sure

634
00:37:03,092 --> 00:37:05,094
that each secret is different.

635
00:37:05,511 --> 00:37:07,179
How is that supposed to help?

636
00:37:08,222 --> 00:37:09,222
It’s like this.

637
00:37:10,057 --> 00:37:11,058
Example...

638
00:37:12,518 --> 00:37:14,228
tell friend number one, you like red.

639
00:37:15,104 --> 00:37:16,731
Tell friend number two, you like blue.

640
00:37:17,481 --> 00:37:19,317
And tell friend number
three, you like green.

641
00:37:19,984 --> 00:37:23,321
Whatever color gets posted tomorrow
on Clark U Confessions,

642
00:37:25,406 --> 00:37:27,992
that’s how you’ll know
which friend betrayed you.

643
00:37:29,201 --> 00:37:31,078
Do you think that’ll work?

644
00:37:31,704 --> 00:37:32,704
Trust me.

645
00:37:32,830 --> 00:37:36,000
That's the only way
to expose the rat among your peers.

646
00:37:37,585 --> 00:37:38,669
Okay!

647
00:37:38,920 --> 00:37:40,463
Thank you so much!

648
00:37:40,671 --> 00:37:42,089
Thank you!

649
00:37:49,180 --> 00:37:50,973
Let’s see how’s it goes out for Madison.

650
00:37:51,557 --> 00:37:52,808
Madison?

651
00:37:53,100 --> 00:37:55,186
You mean, Madonna Barcelon?

652
00:37:55,187 --> 00:38:01,870
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

653
00:37:55,895 --> 00:37:56,895
Yeah.

654
00:37:57,939 --> 00:38:01,108
Wait, I thought
you weren’t interested in that case?

655
00:38:01,651 --> 00:38:03,736
You even yawned at first.

656
00:38:04,320 --> 00:38:06,489
Why do you suddenly seem
concerned about her?

657
00:38:08,032 --> 00:38:09,032
Well...

658
00:38:09,408 --> 00:38:11,619
the moment she mentioned
about the student council...

659
00:38:12,244 --> 00:38:13,537
my interest was piqued.

660
00:38:14,997 --> 00:38:16,831
Her popularity is a threat

661
00:38:16,832 --> 00:38:19,835
to anyone who wants to run
for the council.

662
00:38:20,378 --> 00:38:23,923
But that demolition job feels too early.

663
00:38:24,799 --> 00:38:26,342
The election is still far away.

664
00:38:28,761 --> 00:38:30,346
Kill the fire before it spreads.

665
00:38:31,013 --> 00:38:32,640
Pluck the weed before it grows.

666
00:38:33,432 --> 00:38:36,018
If I plan to run
for student council next year,

667
00:38:36,519 --> 00:38:40,064
I’d find out who my rivals are
and look for their weaknesses.

668
00:38:41,190 --> 00:38:43,025
If this is really about the election,

669
00:38:44,235 --> 00:38:45,236
her opponent

670
00:38:45,695 --> 00:38:47,279
must be a forward-thinker.

671
00:38:48,698 --> 00:38:51,617
They used her friends
to dig up some dirt on her.

672
00:38:53,369 --> 00:38:54,745
We don’t know that yet.

673
00:38:56,122 --> 00:38:57,122
Friendship...

674
00:38:57,331 --> 00:38:58,666
it’s a double edged-sword.

675
00:39:13,222 --> 00:39:14,932
That’s why I don’t want friends.

676
00:39:18,436 --> 00:39:19,979
They are all just excess baggage.

677
00:39:21,564 --> 00:39:22,564
Is that why...

678
00:39:23,816 --> 00:39:25,067
you don’t have friends?

679
00:39:26,027 --> 00:39:28,738
Because you see them as a burden?

680
00:39:38,748 --> 00:39:40,249
Once you befriend someone...

681
00:39:42,043 --> 00:39:43,961
you allow yourself to be vulnerable.

682
00:39:45,296 --> 00:39:47,757
And they'd use that vulnerability
against you

683
00:39:48,132 --> 00:39:52,219
someday once friends turn to enemies.

684
00:39:54,513 --> 00:39:56,557
Have you always believed that?

685
00:39:57,850 --> 00:39:59,393
Chief Estrada said...

686
00:40:00,144 --> 00:40:01,937
you were approachable before.

687
00:40:02,897 --> 00:40:04,982
I heard you used to have an assistant.

688
00:40:06,358 --> 00:40:07,443
I assume that

689
00:40:07,693 --> 00:40:10,821
she was also a member of the Q.E.D. Club.

690
00:40:16,160 --> 00:40:17,745
Friendship comes at a cost.

691
00:40:18,370 --> 00:40:19,705
If you’re willing to pay for it,

692
00:40:20,831 --> 00:40:22,249
go ahead and make some friends.

693
00:40:23,751 --> 00:40:24,752
But if not,

694
00:40:27,088 --> 00:40:28,714
it’s better to stay away from people.

695
00:40:44,146 --> 00:40:45,606
I just want to help you.

696
00:40:45,981 --> 00:40:48,275
You won’t gain anything by joining that.

697
00:40:49,151 --> 00:40:50,945
Leave the Q.E.D. Club.

698
00:40:51,695 --> 00:40:54,573
Staying close to Loki
will only bring you tragedy.

699
00:40:56,450 --> 00:40:59,703
Hasn’t he told you
what happened to the former member?

700
00:41:00,538 --> 00:41:02,748
I see he hasn’t told you about her.

701
00:41:03,457 --> 00:41:04,667
And yet you’re here,

702
00:41:05,459 --> 00:41:06,877
risking your life for him?

703
00:41:14,677 --> 00:41:17,095
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

704
00:41:17,096 --> 00:41:20,141
- O to the M to the G!
- What happened?

705
00:41:20,558 --> 00:41:21,725
I know now

706
00:41:22,017 --> 00:41:24,728
who the traitor is among my friends.

707
00:41:25,855 --> 00:41:27,022
Congratulations.

708
00:41:27,606 --> 00:41:30,943
Thank you. I did exactly
what you told me to do.

709
00:41:31,026 --> 00:41:32,153
Now I know...

710
00:41:32,361 --> 00:41:34,905
it’s that Geraldine bitch!

711
00:41:35,531 --> 00:41:36,531
So…

712
00:41:37,366 --> 00:41:38,367
what did you do?

713
00:41:39,368 --> 00:41:41,120
I confronted her.

714
00:41:41,871 --> 00:41:43,414
How could you do this to me?

715
00:41:43,539 --> 00:41:45,916
After everything I did for you?

716
00:41:45,958 --> 00:41:50,462
I treated you like my sister,
and this is what you do to me?

717
00:41:50,963 --> 00:41:52,339
I’m sorry, Madonna!

718
00:41:53,340 --> 00:41:56,010
I never meant to do that to you.

719
00:41:56,343 --> 00:41:58,469
Then why did you do it?

720
00:41:58,470 --> 00:42:00,222
Someone’s blackmailing me!

721
00:42:00,764 --> 00:42:02,891
They said they have my private photos.

722
00:42:02,892 --> 00:42:06,020
If I didn’t do it to you,
they’d spread it.

723
00:42:06,437 --> 00:42:07,396
I’m sorry...

724
00:42:07,396 --> 00:42:08,396
Stop it!

725
00:42:08,606 --> 00:42:09,606
Blackmail?

726
00:42:10,107 --> 00:42:11,650
That’s what she’s claiming.

727
00:42:11,901 --> 00:42:13,861
But it doesn’t matter anymore.

728
00:42:14,195 --> 00:42:17,323
Our friendship is over!

729
00:42:18,032 --> 00:42:19,575
I can’t trust her anymore.

730
00:42:20,492 --> 00:42:21,492
Well...

731
00:42:21,660 --> 00:42:22,661
next time,

732
00:42:23,078 --> 00:42:24,496
choose your friends wisely.

733
00:42:25,414 --> 00:42:26,957
Not everyone close to you…

734
00:42:27,374 --> 00:42:28,584
is your friend.

735
00:42:29,168 --> 00:42:31,211
Well, thank you for the reminder.

736
00:42:31,212 --> 00:42:34,632
But I came here to give you these.

737
00:42:34,840 --> 00:42:38,551
As a token of my appreciation...

738
00:42:38,552 --> 00:42:42,097
Wait, it’s hard to choose.

739
00:42:42,431 --> 00:42:43,974
This one’s good!

740
00:42:44,892 --> 00:42:46,643
Ma…

741
00:42:46,644 --> 00:42:48,145
do…

742
00:42:48,479 --> 00:42:49,647
nna!

743
00:42:49,939 --> 00:42:53,692
Hugs and kisses for you.

744
00:42:54,235 --> 00:42:55,318
And one more thing!

745
00:42:55,319 --> 00:42:56,904
Ma...

746
00:42:57,029 --> 00:42:58,780
do... nna!

747
00:42:58,781 --> 00:43:00,324
Perfect!

748
00:43:00,532 --> 00:43:02,701
Thak you so much!

749
00:43:03,619 --> 00:43:05,829
Why on earth do you think
we’d want one of these?

750
00:43:06,914 --> 00:43:08,332
Thank you for this, Madonna!

751
00:43:08,749 --> 00:43:10,918
Welcome!

752
00:43:11,001 --> 00:43:13,671
I’ll go ahead! Bye!

753
00:43:13,712 --> 00:43:16,173
Madonna, you go, girl!

754
00:43:19,468 --> 00:43:20,844
Well, that was something.

755
00:43:25,349 --> 00:43:26,350
What are you do...

756
00:43:27,017 --> 00:43:28,102
Loki!

757
00:43:42,157 --> 00:43:44,285
At least we have another solved case
this week.

758
00:43:45,286 --> 00:43:47,121
Don’t forget to update the Chronicles.

759
00:43:48,122 --> 00:43:49,122
Okay.

760
00:43:49,623 --> 00:43:51,166
I’ll do it later when I get home.

761
00:43:53,752 --> 00:43:54,752
Excuse me.

762
00:43:54,962 --> 00:43:55,962
Bathroom break?

763
00:44:19,111 --> 00:44:21,447
Looks like you’re enjoying his company.

764
00:44:21,989 --> 00:44:25,743
Are you drawn to him
or to the mysteries surrounding him?

765
00:44:26,618 --> 00:44:28,162
Are you following me?

766
00:44:28,829 --> 00:44:30,456
If you have a problem with Loki...

767
00:44:30,706 --> 00:44:32,541
why don’t you just tell him?

768
00:44:34,877 --> 00:44:36,211
I’m here to help you...

769
00:44:36,587 --> 00:44:37,587
not him.

770
00:44:37,838 --> 00:44:39,965
Well, you’re not helping.

771
00:44:40,257 --> 00:44:42,217
Your presence is getting annoying.

772
00:44:42,718 --> 00:44:45,012
And why are you so obsessed with him?

773
00:44:45,679 --> 00:44:47,555
Well, you leave me with no other choice

774
00:44:47,556 --> 00:44:49,683
but to tell you a thing or two about Loki.

775
00:44:50,184 --> 00:44:52,519
Information that not many people know.

776
00:44:52,853 --> 00:44:53,854
For what?

777
00:44:54,563 --> 00:44:57,816
So you can decide
whether to stay with him and his club

778
00:44:58,150 --> 00:45:00,110
or walk away and save yourself.

779
00:45:02,237 --> 00:45:03,364
So, game?

780
00:45:06,075 --> 00:45:07,284
You’re curious, aren’t you?

781
00:45:08,118 --> 00:45:09,286
Because if not...

782
00:45:09,745 --> 00:45:11,288
you should’ve walked out already.

783
00:45:12,998 --> 00:45:13,998
Fine.

784
00:45:14,416 --> 00:45:15,416
What is it?

785
00:45:16,085 --> 00:45:18,337
Do you know Loki’s favorite song?

786
00:45:18,670 --> 00:45:19,963
How would I know?

787
00:45:20,672 --> 00:45:22,049
Do you know Rhea?

788
00:45:22,466 --> 00:45:23,466
No.

789
00:45:24,885 --> 00:45:26,303
But, accidentally...

790
00:45:26,887 --> 00:45:29,223
I saw Loki’s email to her.

791
00:45:30,057 --> 00:45:32,475
Is Loki still emailing her until now?

792
00:45:32,476 --> 00:45:34,728
Let's just get straight
to the point, please?

793
00:45:36,146 --> 00:45:38,982
It’s better if Loki
tells you everything himself.

794
00:45:39,441 --> 00:45:40,776
But for that to happen…

795
00:45:41,610 --> 00:45:44,154
you have to listen carefully
to what I’ll say.

796
00:45:47,491 --> 00:45:50,035
Sing his favorite song while he’s around.

797
00:45:50,411 --> 00:45:51,745
Make sure he hears it.

798
00:45:52,704 --> 00:45:53,747
Favorite song?

799
00:45:55,582 --> 00:45:58,752
Yes, and his favorite song is...

800
00:45:59,837 --> 00:46:04,967
♪ Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star. ♪

801
00:46:05,467 --> 00:46:10,389
♪ How I wonder what you are? ♪

802
00:46:10,764 --> 00:46:11,432
Stop it.

803
00:46:11,433 --> 00:46:16,061
♪ Up above the world so high. ♪

804
00:46:16,770 --> 00:46:21,357
♪ Like a diamond in the sky ♪

805
00:46:21,358 --> 00:46:22,442
I said stop it!

806
00:46:22,443 --> 00:46:27,448
When the blazing sun is gone.

807
00:46:27,906 --> 00:46:31,951
When the nothing shines upo...

808
00:46:31,952 --> 00:46:32,995
I said stop!

809
00:46:36,081 --> 00:46:39,751
I don’t know if it’s a coincidence
or you meant to sing it in my presence.

810
00:46:40,586 --> 00:46:42,379
Did someone tell you how much I hate it?

811
00:46:42,963 --> 00:46:44,882
Or did you do that on purpose?

812
00:46:45,591 --> 00:46:46,591
Whoa.

813
00:46:46,717 --> 00:46:47,717
Easy there.

814
00:46:48,051 --> 00:46:49,595
It’s just a nursery rhyme.

815
00:46:49,928 --> 00:46:51,472
To you it’s just a nursery rhyme,

816
00:46:51,930 --> 00:46:53,932
but every time I hear that song,

817
00:46:54,266 --> 00:46:55,601
it’s like a thousand knives

818
00:46:56,018 --> 00:46:57,143
stabbing my ears!

819
00:46:57,144 --> 00:46:58,479
That’s how painful it is!

820
00:47:04,735 --> 00:47:05,735
Why?

821
00:47:06,987 --> 00:47:08,447
Did something bad happen

822
00:47:09,281 --> 00:47:10,407
when you were a kid

823
00:47:10,991 --> 00:47:12,367
while singing that song?

824
00:47:15,704 --> 00:47:16,704
Loki...

825
00:47:17,498 --> 00:47:18,957
what really happened?

826
00:47:20,375 --> 00:47:21,418
You can tell me.

827
00:47:22,669 --> 00:47:24,129
I promise I’ll understand.

828
00:47:26,173 --> 00:47:27,173
Talk to me.

829
00:47:28,217 --> 00:47:29,467
This is a safe space.

830
00:47:29,468 --> 00:47:30,468
Fine!

831
00:47:31,011 --> 00:47:32,221
You wanna know the truth?

832
00:47:33,388 --> 00:47:35,182
When I hear that song,

833
00:47:35,474 --> 00:47:37,392
memories come rushing back.

834
00:47:40,062 --> 00:47:41,939
Memories I want to bury...

835
00:47:42,189 --> 00:47:43,189
and forget!

836
00:47:44,358 --> 00:47:47,486
That song was playing
when I saw her in front of me…

837
00:47:49,321 --> 00:47:50,697
with no life left.

838
00:47:53,700 --> 00:47:54,826
I couldn’t do anything!

839
00:47:56,203 --> 00:47:58,789
I just stood there
and listened to that song!

840
00:47:59,456 --> 00:48:02,376
And I saw my friend’s body
with no life in it anymore.

841
00:48:03,544 --> 00:48:05,629
My one and only friend!

842
00:48:08,298 --> 00:48:09,298
I’m sorry...

843
00:48:12,302 --> 00:48:13,554
I'm really sorry.

844
00:48:25,816 --> 00:48:28,026
Now that you’ve learned
a bit of my past...

845
00:48:30,445 --> 00:48:31,738
are you satisfied?

846
00:48:33,740 --> 00:48:34,992
Do you wanna know more?

847
00:48:36,201 --> 00:48:37,910
Do you want me to tell you

848
00:48:37,911 --> 00:48:41,123
how many stabs her fragile body sustained?

849
00:48:46,128 --> 00:48:47,128
That man...

850
00:48:50,382 --> 00:48:52,134
Moriya...

851
00:48:52,175 --> 00:48:53,175
M.

852
00:48:53,677 --> 00:48:54,677
Mori...

853
00:48:55,262 --> 00:48:56,262
Moriya...

854
00:48:57,764 --> 00:48:59,099
whatever his real name is.

855
00:49:01,893 --> 00:49:03,270
He’s the one behind it.

856
00:49:05,314 --> 00:49:06,648
I’m sorry, Loki.

857
00:49:09,067 --> 00:49:10,152
If I only knew...

858
00:49:11,320 --> 00:49:12,800
that things would turn out like this,

859
00:49:14,489 --> 00:49:16,325
I wouldn’t have sung it.

860
00:49:25,083 --> 00:49:26,376
That friend of yours..

861
00:49:29,463 --> 00:49:30,631
She's Rhea...

862
00:49:32,299 --> 00:49:33,299
right?

863
00:49:45,395 --> 00:49:47,981
Why did I even take Maggie’s advice?

864
00:49:48,607 --> 00:49:51,193
Now Loki might never forgive me.

865
00:49:54,613 --> 00:49:58,075
But at least now I know
what really happened to Rhea

866
00:49:58,367 --> 00:50:00,702
and the past Loki has been hiding.

867
00:50:04,206 --> 00:50:06,625
I just probably need to say sorry to him.

868
00:50:06,875 --> 00:50:08,877
Since we’re meeting tomorrow,

869
00:50:09,127 --> 00:50:11,380
I’ll have more time to talk to him.

870
00:50:26,186 --> 00:50:27,186
Loki..

871
00:50:28,689 --> 00:50:30,482
I just want to say sorry

872
00:50:31,316 --> 00:50:32,317
for what happened.

873
00:50:35,320 --> 00:50:36,320
Loki.

874
00:50:36,988 --> 00:50:38,031
Come on!

875
00:50:38,990 --> 00:50:40,450
Notice me!

876
00:50:42,953 --> 00:50:44,162
Am I hearing things?

877
00:50:46,665 --> 00:50:48,333
Maybe my ex-roommates were right.

878
00:50:49,710 --> 00:50:51,294
There might be a real ghost in here...

879
00:50:51,920 --> 00:50:54,715
calling my name,
making strange noises.

880
00:50:56,675 --> 00:50:58,593
Or maybe it’s just a wind.

881
00:50:58,719 --> 00:51:00,178
Are you for real?

882
00:51:00,721 --> 00:51:01,721
Wow!

883
00:51:01,763 --> 00:51:03,765
That's real mature of you, Loki.

884
00:51:04,558 --> 00:51:06,768
If there’s a real ghost in here,
leave me alone.

885
00:51:08,353 --> 00:51:10,021
I don’t want your presence.

886
00:51:10,856 --> 00:51:12,482
I don’t even want to hear your voice.

887
00:51:13,024 --> 00:51:14,024
Fine.

888
00:51:14,776 --> 00:51:16,236
If that's what you want.

889
00:51:30,125 --> 00:51:31,126
Loki.

890
00:51:32,294 --> 00:51:34,254
Don’t you plan on talking to me anymore?

891
00:51:35,464 --> 00:51:36,840
I’m warning you...

892
00:51:37,758 --> 00:51:39,384
if you don't talk to me,

893
00:51:40,010 --> 00:51:42,137
I will be resigning from the Q.E.D. Club.

894
00:51:43,555 --> 00:51:45,182
Is there a ghost here in the clubroom?

895
00:51:47,726 --> 00:51:50,854
Well, maybe the apartment spirit
followed me all the way here.

896
00:51:51,313 --> 00:51:52,313
Or maybe...

897
00:51:52,898 --> 00:51:55,358
I’m just imagining things
because I'm sleepy.

898
00:51:58,445 --> 00:51:59,696
I think I’ll buy some coffee.

899
00:52:37,567 --> 00:52:40,402
Are you okay, ma'am?
Haven’t you talked yet?

900
00:52:40,403 --> 00:52:41,738
No, I'm okay.

901
00:52:42,072 --> 00:52:43,072
Thank you.

902
00:52:45,492 --> 00:52:46,492
Wait.

903
00:52:47,410 --> 00:52:48,495
Do you know me?

904
00:53:36,960 --> 00:53:38,503
Help!

905
00:53:38,795 --> 00:53:40,254
You’re finally awake!

906
00:53:40,255 --> 00:53:42,173
We gave Loki fifteen minutes.

907
00:53:42,591 --> 00:53:46,052
If he finds you,
we’ll let you stay in the club.

908
00:53:52,350 --> 00:53:53,601
Hey! Are you okay?

909
00:53:53,602 --> 00:53:55,103
There’s someone else behind this.

910
00:53:55,478 --> 00:53:57,271
The person behind your abduction

911
00:53:57,272 --> 00:53:58,940
is someone who reeks of evil

912
00:53:59,357 --> 00:54:00,733
and relentless manipulation.

913
00:54:00,734 --> 00:54:01,985
Welcome to…

914
00:54:02,777 --> 00:54:03,986
the White Hostel!

915
00:54:03,987 --> 00:54:05,322
Are you in the White Hostel?

916
00:54:05,572 --> 00:54:06,656
What a coincidence.

917
00:54:08,033 --> 00:54:09,034
This is Officer…

918
00:54:09,451 --> 00:54:10,952
- Bastien Montreal.
- Chief.

919
00:54:13,747 --> 00:54:15,665
So, who could that person be?
